"title": "7775: prophets, lives of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7775: prophets, lives of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God called individuals from differing backgrounds to speak as prophets on his behalf, sometimes in difficult circumstances.</p>\n<h2>The backgrounds of the prophets</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:1-Exod2:10\">EXO 2:1–2:10</a> <em>Moses was brought up in the Egyptian royal court</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:21-1Sam1:28\">1SA 1:21–1:28</a> <em>Samuel was a temple servant at Shiloh</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:19-1Kgs19:21\">1KI 19:19–19:21</a> <em>Elisha was a farmer</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:3\">EZK 1:3</a> <em>Ezekiel was a priest living in exile in Babylonia.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:1\">AMO 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos7:14\">AMO 7:14</a></p>\n<h2>The calling of the prophets</h2>\n<h3>Their initial encounter with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1-Isa6:4\">ISA 6:1–6:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:1-Exod3:6\">EXO 3:1–3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:4-Ezek1:28\">EZK 1:4–1:28</a></p>\n<h3>God communicating his call</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:4-Jer1:5\">JER 1:4–1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:8-Isa6:10\">ISA 6:8–6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek2:3-Ezek3:5\">EZK 2:3–3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:1\">JON 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:1\">JON 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>Their response to God's call</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:6-Jer1:10\">JER 1:6–1:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:11-Exod3:12\">EXO 3:11–3:12</a></p>\n<h2>The family life of the prophets</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:1-Jer16:4\">JER 16:1–16:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:3\">ISA 7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:1-Isa8:4\">ISA 8:1–8:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:15-Ezek24:24\">EZK 24:15–24:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos1:2-Hos1:11\">HOS 1:2–1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:1-Hos3:5\">HOS 3:1–3:5</a></p>\n<h2>The hardships faced by prophets</h2>\n<h3>Persecution</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:32-Heb11:38\">HEB 11:32–11:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:52\">ACT 7:52</a></p>\n<h3>Reviling and beating</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:22-Luke6:23\">LUK 6:22–6:23</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:11-Matt5:12\">MAT 5:11–5:12</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:1-Jer20:2\">JER 20:1–20:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:10\">JAS 5:10</a></p>\n<h3>Imprisonment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer37:11-Jer37:16\">JER 37:11–37:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:26-1Kgs22:27\">1KI 22:26–22:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:25-2Chr18:26\">2CH 18:25–18:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:10\">2CH 16:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer37:21\">JER 37:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:6-Jer38:13\">JER 38:6–38:13</a></p>\n<h3>Killing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:14\">1KI 19:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:4\">1KI 18:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:13\">1KI 18:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:2\">1KI 19:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer26:8-Jer26:11\">JER 26:8–26:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer26:20-Jer26:23\">JER 26:20–26:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:29-Matt23:31\">MAT 23:29–23:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:37\">MAT 23:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:34\">LUK 13:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:47-Luke11:49\">LUK 11:47–11:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:4-1Thess2:15\">1TH 2:4–2:15</a></p>\n<h2>The death of prophets</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:1-Deut34:8\">DEU 34:1–34:8</a> <em>Moses</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:3\">1SA 28:3</a> <em>Samuel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs2:11-2Kgs2:12\">2KI 2:11–2:12</a> <em>Elijah did not die but was taken up in a chariot of fire.</em></p>",
